h3. Resolution
{panel}
(/) This bug is resolved on Service Desk version 2 and above with agent based license. 
(!) You have to update UPM to the latest version available to avoid JSD-795.
{panel}

Currently we create a service desk project the project roles for *Service Desk Customer* and *Service Desk Team* will be automatically assigned to _jira-users_ as you can see the following screenshots:
{panel}
!1.jpg!
{panel}

It will be better if we could implement a default group option for these roles instead since most of the customer would prefer a customized group being added instead of the _jira-users_ group.

h4. Customer feedback:
{panel}
We are running a large JIRA instance which are using by around more then 200 project teams and we do not want any global default access (like access to "jira-group") to newly create Service Desk project. We will explicitly provide customized access to newly created Service Desk project (based on project team requirement).
{panel}

h3. Steps to Reproduce:
# Install JIRA and Confluence;
# Install JIRA Service Desk;
# Create a Test project, Service Desk and Space;
# Create an Application Link between JIRA and Confluence;
# Add a knowledge base linking to the *Demonstration Space* on the *Demonstration Service Desk Customer Portal*;
# Change Confluence's URL;
# And update the Application Link to use the new URL.
# The Service Desk to KB link is not automatically updated
# The UI can't delete the KB link from the service desk

h3. Expected Behavior:
JIRA Service Desk would show the new URL when showing Confluence's pages on the Demonstration Customer Portal.

h3. Actual Behavior:
JIRA still uses the old application link URL.

h4. Workaround:
[Knowledge Base searches still use the old Application Link URL on the Customer Portal|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/SDKB/Knowledge+Base+searches+still+use+the+old+Application+Link+URL+on+the+Customer+Portal]

